VULN.TITLE: Google Chrome WebP Heap Buffer Overflow
VULN.DIAGNOSIS: Google Chrome versions prior to 116.0.5845.187 contain a heap buffer overflow in WebP image processing that could allow remote code execution.
VULN.CONSEQUENCE: A remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code in the context of the browser process.

VULN.TITLE: Microsoft Office and Windows HTML Remote Code Execution
VULN.DIAGNOSIS: Microsoft Office and Windows HTML components are vulnerable to remote code execution when processing specially crafted documents.
VULN.CONSEQUENCE: An attacker could execute arbitrary code with the privileges of the victim user by convincing them to open a malicious document.

VULN.TITLE: OpenSSH Remote Code Execution
VULN.DIAGNOSIS: OpenSSH versions before 9.3p2 are vulnerable to remote code execution through ssh-agent forwarding.
VULN.CONSEQUENCE: A remote attacker with access to the ssh-agent socket could potentially execute arbitrary code on the target system.

VULN.TITLE: Postfix SMTP Smuggling
VULN.DIAGNOSIS: Postfix versions before 3.8.2 are vulnerable to SMTP smuggling attacks that can bypass security controls.
VULN.CONSEQUENCE: An attacker could bypass email security filters and deliver malicious content to recipients.

VULN.TITLE: Apache ActiveMQ Remote Code Execution
VULN.DIAGNOSIS: Apache ActiveMQ versions 5.18.0 through 5.18.2 are vulnerable to remote code execution through deserialization of untrusted data.
VULN.CONSEQUENCE: A remote unauthenticated attacker could execute arbitrary code on the ActiveMQ server.

VULN.TITLE: JetBrains TeamCity Authentication Bypass
VULN.DIAGNOSIS: JetBrains TeamCity versions before 2023.05.4 contain an authentication bypass vulnerability that allows unauthorized access to the server.
VULN.CONSEQUENCE: An unauthenticated attacker could gain administrative access to the TeamCity server and potentially execute code.
